Ah, that's a good question. I would say probably the level one is you've got one, maybe a couple

00:32:32.800 --> 00:32:37.680
of data scientists, and you're really just looking for them to derive insights. This is probably a

00:32:37.680 --> 00:32:45.920
company that doesn't have a lot of existing analytics support. They're making decisions based

00:32:45.920 --> 00:32:52.239
on experience or domain knowledge or things like that, and they really don't have a data-driven

00:32:52.239 --> 00:33:00.160
approach at all. And so they hire data scientists and they say, well, what does the data say about

00:33:00.160 --> 00:33:06.719
the decisions I'm trying to make? How could I improve upon a very heuristic based decision

00:33:06.719 --> 00:33:14.479
making process? And there, I think, the bar is pretty low. You could use a basic data set,

00:33:14.479 --> 00:33:19.839
some pretty basic modeling techniques, and probably improve upon what they're doing.

