because the models that we build, we don't just build them in a lab, right? They impact lives.

00:35:15.840 --> 00:35:24.879
You know, they impact lives. So essentially, in this case, whatever the model predicts is

00:35:24.879 --> 00:35:31.919
impacting, for example, I'm assuming the rate that someone pays for insurance, right? So

