so I, you know, I can work that in sometimes in the margins, but professionally honestly just

01:01:23.120 --> 01:01:28.080
don't have the time for it. So that, I mean that's, I think one of the choices you make

01:01:28.879 --> 01:01:32.879
when you decide to go into data science leadership versus, you know, being a senior technical

01:01:32.879 --> 01:01:36.959
contributor or something like that, is you recognize that your hands-on time is going to

01:01:36.959 --> 01:01:43.439
diminish the higher that you advance. But I think it's important to

01:01:43.600 --> 01:01:48.080
invest enough in at least understanding the technologies. I mean data science is a rapidly

01:01:48.080 --> 01:01:53.840
developing space, technologies, platforms, tools, methodologies are always moving. I think as a

01:01:53.840 --> 01:01:58.479
leader you need to invest enough of your time to understand how to make good decisions

01:01:59.600 --> 01:02:06.159
in your job and how to utilize those technologies, where to invest, and those sorts of things to do

01:02:06.159 --> 01:02:11.439
that well. So you can't completely, you know, ignore what's going on. I think you have to

01:02:11.679 --> 01:02:14.239
what's going on. I think you have to maintain some connection

01:02:16.000 --> 01:02:19.919
